03534nam a22006135i 9780271062358DE-B159720220524034747.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220524t20212013pau    fo  d z      eng d  a97802710623587 a10.1515/97802710623582doi  a(DE-B1597)583674  a(OCoLC)1266228312  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  apaucUS-PA 7aART0150802bisacsh04a751.730945629999951 ade Jong, Jan L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Power and the Glorification :bPapal Pretensions and the Art of Propaganda in the Fifteenth and Sixteenth Centuries /cJan L. de Jong. 1aUniversity Park, PA : bPenn State University Press, c[2021] 4cÂ©2013  a1 online resource (208 p.) :b31 color/93 b&w illustrations  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aFocusing on a turbulent time in the history of the Roman Catholic Church, The Power and the Glorification considers how, in the fifteenth and sixteenth centuries, the papacy employed the visual arts to help reinforce Catholic power structures. All means of propaganda were deployed to counter the papacy's eroding authority in the wake of the Great Schism of 1378 and in response to the upheaval surrounding the Protestant Reformation a century later. In the Vatican and elsewhere in Rome, extensive decorative cycles were commissioned to represent the strength of the church and historical justifications for its supreme authority. Replicating the contemporary viewer's experience is central to De Jong's approach, and he encourages readers to consider the works through fifteenth- and sixteenth-century eyes. De Jong argues that most visitors would only have had a limited knowledge of the historical events represented in these works, and they would likely have accepted (or been intended to accept) what they saw at face value. With that end in mind, the painters' advisors did their best to "manipulate" the viewer accordingly, and De Jong discusses their strategies and methods.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aART / History / Renaissance.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271062358?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271062358423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271062358/original  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK